      "id": "bug-034",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-23T03:57:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Sustained Premature close bursts on Google OAuth token endpoint from Fly syd region exhaust 5 server-side retries (~16.5s total wait). User still sees SHEET_WRITE_FAILED.",
      "file": "src/pages/api/renew/checkout-pm.ts, checkout-am.ts",
      "root_cause": "gaxios 6.7.1 (used by googleapis/google-auth-library) has a deprecated HTTPS adapter that drops connections during Google OAuth token fetch. Both gaxios and google-auth-library are ARCHIVED — no upstream fix coming. Server-side retry wrapper at renewal-sheet.ts layer fires as designed (verified via logs: oauth_token_refresh attempt 1+2 visible) but the same gaxios adapter is hit on every retry, so all attempts fail in a sustained burst. Raw Node.js https.request from Fly reaches oauth2.googleapis.com in 400ms — only gaxios is broken.",
      "fix": "Set SHEET_WRITE_FAILED retryable:true so the client form can retry on click. A fresh client request almost always succeeds because the burst has cleared. Server-side retry stays in place as first defence (handles 95%+ of transient drops). For sustained outages, the only durable fix is bypassing gaxios: call https://oauth2.googleapis.com/oauth2/v4/token with native fetch, cache the JWT token, then pass cached token to google.sheets({version, auth}). Out of scope for current ticket.",
      "tags": [
        "gaxios",
        "premature-close",
        "archived",
        "retryable",
        "staging",
        "client-retry",
        "workaround"
      ],
